### Network Device Inventory API Tests
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension or similar tool

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Get API Information
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### 2. Get All Devices
GET {{baseUrl}}/devices

### 3. Get Device by ID (replace :id with actual ID, e.g., 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/devices/1

### 4. Create New Device
POST {{baseUrl}}/devices
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "hostname": "router-test-01",
  "ip_address": "192.168.1.200",
  "device_type": "Router",
  "location": "Test Lab",
  "status": "active",
  "notes": "Testing API endpoint"
}

### 5. Update Device (replace :id with actual ID)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/devices/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "status": "maintenance",
  "notes": "Updated via API test"
}

### 6. Delete Device (replace :id with actual ID)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/devices/6

